description: This walk climbs to Galtymore mountain in the Galty Mountains area of County Tipperary. The mountain stands at a height of 917.9 metres (3,011 ft 6 in) making it the highest of the Galty Mountains. The walk starts from the parking area at Glengarra Wood and then heads south passing the picturesque Lough Curra . The route then turns east heading up to the summit of Galtymore where you can enjoy some wonderful views over the surrounding area.
